sequenceDiagram
    participant CP as Charge Point (OCTT)
    participant CS as Central System (SUT)

    Note over CP,CS: Test Case: TC_048_2_CSMS
    Note over CP,CS: Reservation of a Connector - Occupied
    Note over CP,CS: Table 169, pages 144-145 (CompliancyTestTool-TestCaseDocument 2025-11)
    Note over CP,CS: Prerequisite: Central System supports Reservation feature profile

    Note over CP: [EV driver plugs in cable]

    CP->>CS: 1. StatusNotification.req (status: Preparing, connectorId: <Configured>)
    Note over CP: Validation: status must be Preparing, connectorId must be <Configured ConnectorId>
    CS-->>CP: 2. StatusNotification.conf

    CS->>CP: 3. ReserveNow.req
    Note left of CS: connectorId: connectorId from step 1<br/>idTag: <Configured Valid IdTag><br/>reservationId: <unique id> (inferred from OCPP spec)<br/>expiryDate: <future timestamp> (inferred from OCPP spec)
    Note left of CS: Validation: connectorId from step 1, idTag is <Configured Valid IdTag>

    CP-->>CS: 4. ReserveNow.conf (status: Occupied)
    Note over CP: Validation: status must be Occupied

    Note over CP,CS: Expected: CS accepts the Reservation message with the not Accepted status
